===Noun===
'''laughter'''

#A [[movement]] (usually involuntary) of the muscles of the face, particularly of the lips, with a peculiar [[expression]] of the eyes, indicating merriment, satisfaction, or derision, and usually attended by a sonorous and interrupted expulsion of air from the lungs.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*The act of '''laughter''', which is a sweet contraction of the muscles of the face, and a pleasant agitation of the vocal organs, is not merely, or totally within the jurisdiction of ourselves. - [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sir_Thomas_Browne Sir Thomas Browne]
#:*Archly the maiden smiled, and with eyes overrunning with '''laughter''' - [http://en2.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henry_Wadsworth_Longfellow Henry Wadsworth Longfellow]
# The sound produced by air so expelled.

